abtp.name: bt.P
abtp.footer: Invuln: 1~10 Upper Body. +2 oB on earliest Stance Cancel.

abtd.name: Kahn Schild
abtd.footer: Invul: 1~18 Full. Counters strikes and reflects projectiles. When reflecting a projectile from close-up, it will transition into the counter-attack instead. If too far for counter attack, opponent will be staggered instead.

abt214k.name: Gländzendes Dunkel
abt214k.footer: Stays in Backturn Stance if [K] is held.

abt214h.name: Blitzschlag
abt214h.footer: Stays in Backturn Stance if [H] is held.

a632146h.name: Liedenschaft des Dirigenten
a632146h.footer: Invul: 1~18 Full. Interruptible between 4th and 5th(Final) hit.

a5k.name: 5K
a5k.footer: Gatling 6H combos at Blood lv2 or higher.

acs.name: c.S
acs.footer: On Block, Gatlings 5H and 2H are true blockstrings at Blood lv2 or higher.

afs.name: f.S
afs.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Hit over 6s (-7.2/300). Cancels into f.SS. Gatling 5H and 2H will combo only at Blood lv3.

afss.name: f.SS
afss.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Hit over 6s (-7.2/300). Cancels into f.SSS

afsss.name: f.SSS
afsss.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Block/Hit over 6s (OB -64.8/300, OH -115.2/300)

a5h.name: 5H
a5h.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Block/Hit over 6s (OB -7.2/300, OH -57.6/300). Range, damage, and startup improves with Blood Level.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2s.name: 2S
a2s.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Hit over 6s (-7.2/300). Gatling 5H combos at Blood lv3

a2h.name: 2H
a2h.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Block/Hit over 6s (OB -7.2/300, OH -57.6/300). Range, damage, and startup improves with Blood Level.

ajs.name: j.S
ajs.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Hit over 6s (-7.2/300)

ajh.name: j.H
ajh.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Block/Hit over 6s (OB -7.2/300, OH -57.6/300). Range, damage, and startup improves with Blood Level.

ajd.name: j.D
ajd.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Hit over 6s (-7.2/300)

a6h.name: 6H
a6h.footer: Decreases Blood Gauge on Block/Hit over 6s (OB -7.2/300, OH -57.6/300). Range, damage, and startup improves with Blood Level.

a236s.name: Zarameyuki
a236s.footer: Increases Blood Gauge over 3s (+90/300). Counter-hit Recovery. Cancelable into other specials.

a236k.name: Fukyo
a236k.footer: Invul: 1~25 Above Chest. Increases Blood Gauge over 3s (+43.2/300). Applies significant sliding momentum. Can be special-canceled towards the end of the animation.

a214k.name: Fukyo
a214k.footer: Invul: 1~16 Above Chest. Increases Blood Gauge over 3s (+43.2/300). Applies significant sliding momentum. Can be special-canceled towards the end of the animation.

a214h.name: Kamuriyuki
a214h.footer: Increases Blood Gauge over 3s (+90/300). Airborne Frames 5~12. Cancelable into other specials.

a623h.name: Shizuriyuki
a623h.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when whiffed.. Invuln: 1~15 Upper Body. Increases Blood Gauge over 3s (+90/300). 1st Hit is Cancelable into other specials. Can be followed up with a 2nd attack by pressing H again.

a623hh.name: Shizuriyuki Follow-up
a623hh.footer: This is the optional 2nd hit of Shizuriyuki. Ground-bounces on hit.

a623p.name: Bloodsucking Universe
a623p.footer: Invul: 1~7 Throw. Greatly decreases Blood Gauge over 3s (-280.8/300). Counter-hit Recovery

a632146s.name: Wasureyuki
a632146s.footer: Invul: 1~10 Full. Final Hit significantly decreases Blood Gauge over 6s (194.4/300)

a632146h.name: Wasureyuki
a632146h.footer: Invuln: 1~26 Full. Exits Blood Rage upon use.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2h.name: 2H
a2h.footer: Launches on air-hit, such as from c.S.

a236k.name: Trovão
a236k.footer: Cancels single-hit projectiles, and goes through the rest. Can be low-profiled.

a214s.name: Sol Poente
a214s.footer: Data in [ ] refers to the overall startup of the 2nd kick. The first hit starts up in 4f, but can only hit opponents behind Gio. Can be steered left or right.

aj214s.name: Air Sol Poente
aj214s.footer: Data in [ ] refers to the overall startup of the 2nd kick. The first hit starts up in 4f, but can only hit opponents behind Gio. Can be steered left or right.

a5h.name: 5H
a5h.footer: Hits on both sides of Anji. Forces crouch-state on counter-hit.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2s.name: 2S
a2s.footer: Hits on both sides of Anji.

ajd.name: j.D
ajd.footer: Briefly floats Anji in place before lettin him fall back down. Wall-bounces near corner.

a236p.name: Shitsu
a236p.footer: Frame advantage listed refers to initial hit.

a236k.name: Suigetsu No Hakobi
a236k.footer: Guard Point on frames 10~25 or up to [41] if button is held. Enters 38f invulnerable spin on successful guard. On successful guard of a strike, opponent will be locked into hit-stop for 28f.

a236s.name: Kou
a236s.footer: Data in [ ] refers to held version. Can add Auto-Guard spin to beginning of startup by holding the button down. Cannot hit grounded opponents. Juggles higher on hit when held. 2nd hit guard-crushes.

a236h.name: Fuujin
a236h.footer: Data in [ ] refers to held version. Can add Auto-Guard spin to beginning of startup by holding the button down. Can be kara-canceled on frames 3~16, during the recovery, or the extended startup of the held version.

a236hp.name: Shin: Ichishiki
a236hp.footer: Data in [ ] refers to held version. Can add Auto-Guard spin to beginning of startup by holding the button down. Can be kara-canceled on frames 3~16, during the recovery, or the extended startup of the held version.

a236hk.name: Shin: Ichishiki
a236hk.footer: -12 on block and -9 on hit at earliest cancel from connected Fuujin.

a236hs.name: Nagiha
a236hs.footer: True blockstring at earliest cancel from connected Fuujin .

a632146s.name: Issei Ougi: Sai
a632146s.footer: Being a counter, this super cannot be safe-jumped. When close, Anji will transition into a full 6-hit counter-attack.

a5p.name: 5P
a5p.footer: I-No's fastest normal. Whiffs on crouching opponents.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a6p.name: 6P
a6p.footer: Invul: 1~2 Upper Body, 3~13 Above Knees. HKD on air-hit.

a6h.name: 6H
a6h.footer: First hit causes float-state on ground-hit. Second hit launches opponent away.

a236h.name: H Stroke the Big Tree
a236h.footer: Staggers on hit. HKD on air-hit.

aj236k.name: K Sultry Performance
aj236k.footer: Data in ( ) refers to advantage if you input the button again to bounce up. Data in [ ] refers to advantage if fully charged. Not an overhead.

aj236s.name: S Sultry Performance
aj236s.footer: Data in ( ) refers to advantage if you input the button again to bounce up. Data in [ ] refers to advantage if fully charged. Not an overhead.

aj236h.name: H Sultry Performance
aj236h.footer: Data in ( ) refers to advantage if you input the button again to bounce up. Data in [ ] refers to advantage if fully charged. Not an overhead.

a214p.name: Antidepressant Scale
a214p.footer: Data in [ ] refers to max number of hits. This projectile gains hits as it travels, up to an additional 4 hits. By holding [2] or [8], I-No can influence the Note's trajectory.

aj214p.name: Air Antidepressant Scale
aj214p.footer: Data in [ ] refers to max number of hits. This projectile gains hits as it travels, up to an additional 4 hits. By holding [2] or [8], I-No can influence the Note's trajectory. Counter-hit recovery until landing.

a632146h.name: Megalomania
a632146h.footer: Data in [ ] refers to whiffed, projectile-only version.

a632146s.name: Ultimate Fortissimo
a632146s.footer: Invul: 1~11 Full. Plus on block but has a 42f gap between the 1st and 2nd hit.

aj632146s.name: Air Ultimate Fortissimo
aj632146s.footer: Not invul, but very advantageous on block.

a5p.name: 5P
a5p.footer: Whiffs versus crouching opponents. Lacks rapid-cancel gatling, but is advantageous.

a5k.name: 5K
a5k.footer: Hits Low! Retracts lower hurtbox before striking.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2p.name: 2P
a2p.footer: GL's fastest normal. Lacks rapid-cancel gatling, but is advantageous. Deceptively good anti-air.

a6p.name: 6P
a6p.footer: Invul: 1~2 Upper Body, 3~17 Above Knees. Hits on the 15th frame vs crouching opponents.

a426h.name: 426 Behemoth Typhoon
a426h.footer: GL slowly swings at his opponent from long range. Hits in front of GL on frame 26, which results in the greater on-block advantage listed. Wall-bounces near the corner.

a624h.name: 624 Behemoth Typhoon
a624h.footer: GL quickly swings at his opponent from close range. Combos from most normals at max range.

a268h.name: 268 Behemoth Typhoon
a268h.footer: GL lifts his opponent into the air on hit from close range. Allows for juggles.

a248h.name: 248 Behemoth Typhoon
a248h.footer: GL knocks his opponent behind him. Allows for juggles, at the cost of side-switching.

a684h.name: 684 Behemoth Typhoon
a684h.footer: GL lifts his opponent into the air on hit from long range. Only frames 17~20 have 80% proration.

a486h.name: 486 Behemoth Typhoon
a486h.footer: GL slowly swings with a long-range Overhead. Hits on frame 28 vs standing which results in the greater on-block advantage listed. Frame advantage versus crouching varies by height. Slower than the other overhead but has longer reach and has huge meterless conversions.

a842h.name: 842 Behemoth Typhoon
a842h.footer: GL swings with a Low attack. Hits in front of GL on frame 24, which results in the greater on-block advantage listed. Only frames 14~15 have 90% proration.

a862h.name: 862 Behemoth Typhoon
a862h.footer: GL quickly swings with a short-range Overhead. Hits on frame 21 vs  standing which results in the greater on-block advantage listed. Frame advantage versus crouching varies by height. Shorter ranger and does not give meterless combo, but faster than the other overhead.

aj426h.name: Air 426 Behemoth Typhoon
aj426h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj624h.name: Air 624 Behemoth Typhoon
aj624h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj268h.name: Air 268 Behemoth Typhoon
aj268h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj248h.name: Air 248 Behemoth Typhoon
aj248h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj684h.name: Air 684 Behemoth Typhoon
aj684h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj486h.name: Air 486 Behemoth Typhoon
aj486h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj842h.name: Air 842 Behemoth Typhoon
aj842h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

aj862h.name: 862 Behemoth Typhoon
aj862h.footer: Does not hit overhead. Slows GL's descent.

a214s.name: Thunderbird
a214s.footer: Data in [ ] represents startup of the first hit. GL can act sooner. Security Level affects travel distance and number of hits. Will block projectiles as long as it's active.

a236s.name: Skyfish
a236s.footer: Security Level affects number of hits.

a360p.name: Down With The System
a360p.footer: Invul: 1~14 Full. Can be input as a full circle. Additional inputs result in more damage.

a720p.name: 720 Down With The System
a720p.footer: Invul: 1~19 Full. Data in [ ] represents Clean Hit version, which happens only if the top of the hitbox connects. Can be input as full circles. Additional input results in more damage.

a1080p.name: 1080 Down With The System
a1080p.footer: Invul: 1~24 Full. Data in [ ] represents Clean Hit version, which happens only if the top of the hitbox connects. Can be input as full circles. This version deals max damage.

a236236k.name: Burn It Down
a236236k.footer: Data in [ ] represents startup of the first hit. GL can act sooner. Security Level affects number of hits. Tracks and pulls opponent towards GL. Can pull opponent out of a wall-splat and allows for a re-splat.

a5p.name: 5P
a5p.footer: Jack-O's fastest normal. Whiffs against most crouching opponents. Launches Servants a short distance forward.

a5k.name: 5K
a5k.footer: Launches Servants a long distance forward.

acs.name: c.S
acs.footer: Launches Servants a long distance forward.

afs.name: f.S
afs.footer: Launches Servants a long distance forward.

a5h.name: 5H
a5h.footer: Launches Servants a long distance forward.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged. Launches Servants in an upwards arc forwards.

a2p.name: 2P
a2p.footer: Launches Servants a short distance forward.

a2k.name: 2K
a2k.footer: Launches Servants a short distance forward.

a2s.name: 2S
a2s.footer: Launches Servants in a tall arc.

a2h.name: 2H
a2h.footer: Launches Servants downwards and into an upwards bounce.

a2d.name: 2D
a2d.footer: Invul: 11~34 Upper Body. Launches Servants a long distance forward.

ajp.name: j.P
ajp.footer: Launches Servants a short distance forward.

ajk.name: j.K
ajk.footer: Launches Servants a short distance forward.

ajs.name: j.S
ajs.footer: Can cross up. Launches Servants downwards and into an upwards bounce.

ajh.name: j.H
ajh.footer: Can cross up. Launches Servants a long distance forward.

ajd.name: j.D
ajd.footer: Halts Jack-O's momentum and pushes her backwards. Launches Servants a short distance forward.

a6p.name: 6P
a6p.footer: Invul: ~1 Upper Body, 2~12 Above Knees. Launches Servants a long distance forward.

a6h.name: 6H
a6h.footer: First hit launches opponents. First hit launches Servants in an upwards arc forwards. Second hit launches Servants a long distance forward.

a236p.name: Summon Servant
a236p.footer: Data in [ ] represents values of held version. Requires Servant Gauge. If button is held for a short time, Jack-O will hold on to the Servant. Summoned Servants will disappear after 8 seconds, when hit by the opponent, when hit by Jack-O twice, or when Jack-O herself is hit.

a236p2p.name: Pick Up Servant
a236p2p.footer: Jack-O cannot block while holding a Servant, but can exercise all her mobilty options, including a backwards Run. While Jack-O is holding a Servant, it can make use of her Servant Command specials without needing Servant Gauge. While holding the Servant, Jack-O can perform her Servant Commands without the need of the motion input. Simply press the button associated with the desired Command. As long as Jack-O is holding the Servant, it will not disappear unless Jack-O is hit. However, they will disappear when dropped if their time has passed. It is possible to throw-tech in this stance.

a236p6p.name: Throw Servant
a236p6p.footer: Jack-O throws the Servant she is currently holding in a large arc.

aj236p6p.name: Air Throw Servant
aj236p6p.footer: Jack-O throws the Servant she is currently holding in a large arc.

a236p5d.name: Release Servant
a236p5d.footer: Jack-O drops the Servant she is currently holding directly in front of her.

aj236p5d.name: Air Release Servant
aj236p5d.footer: Jack-O drops the Servant she is currently holding directly in front of her.

a214p.name: Recover Servant
a214p.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Recalls all Servants and refills Servant Gauge.

aj214p.name: Air Recover Servant
aj214p.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Recalls all Servants and refills Servant Gauge.

a214k.name: Attack Command
a214k.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to attack. Can be used while holding a Servant.

aj214k.name: Air Attack Command
aj214k.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to attack. Can be used while holding a Servant.

a214s.name: Defend Command
a214s.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to put up a shield that blocks attacks. If the opponent attacks the shield, they are put in a throwable Guard Crush state. Can be used while holding a Servant. Refunds action cost on successful block.

aj214s.name: Air Defend Command
aj214s.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to put up a shield that blocks attacks. If the opponent attacks the shield, they are put in a throwable Guard Crush state. Can be used while holding a Servant. Refunds action cost on successful block.

a214h.name: Countdown
a214h.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to explode after 3 seconds. The explosion can hit Jack-O and other Servants. Can be used while holding a Servant. Servants counting down will not disappear if hit more than twice by Jack-O. All momentum is halted if the Servant were to explode mid-toss. When blocked, the Explosion causes 30 frames of Blockstun.

aj214h.name: Air Countdown
aj214h.footer: Data in [ ] represents Jack-O's animation. Requires Servant Gauge. Causes all Servants to explode after 3 seconds. The explosion can hit Jack-O and other Servants. Can be used while holding a Servant. Servants counting down will not disappear if hit more than twice by Jack-O. All momentum is halted if the Servant were to explode mid-toss. When blocked, the Explosion causes 30 frames of Blockstun.

a236k.name: Servant Shoot
a236k.footer: Data in [ ] represents Launched Servant. Can be used while holding a Servant. Launches Servants forward at high speed. Cancelable into Jack-O's other specials and supers.

aj236k.name: Air Servant Shoot
aj236k.footer: Data in [ ] represents Launched Servant. Can be used while holding a Servant. Launches Servants forward at high speed. Cancelable into Jack-O's other specials.

a632146p.name: Forever Elysion Driver
a632146p.footer: Invul: 1~12 Full. Can be combo'd into. Can be performed even while holding a Servant.

a236236s.name: S Cheer Servant On
a236236s.footer: The S version gives Servants infinite Guard Point. Both versions can be active at the same time. Can be performed even while holding a Servant.

a236236h.name: H Cheer Servant On
a236236h.footer: The H version makes the Servant Gauge recover very quickly. Both versions can be active at the same time. Can be performed even while holding a Servant.

a5p.name: 5P
a5p.footer: HC's fastest normal. Whiffs on crouching opponents.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2d.name: 2D
a2d.footer: Plus when canceled into Super Focus.

ajs.name: j.S
ajs.footer: Does not consume ammo, despite the visual. Not disjointed, despite the visual.

a6k.name: 6K
a6k.footer: Hits low! 3-frame gap when canceled into from 5K or 2K. Launches airborne opponents upwards. Plus when canceled into Super Focus.

a6s.name: 6S
a6s.footer: 1-frame gap when canceled into from 5K or 2K

aj2k.name: j.2K
aj2k.footer: Landing this attack will automatically bounce Chaos upwards, conserving his double-jump action. Chaos can be steered back or forwards after the bounce.

a236s.name: At The Ready
a236s.footer: Data represents values of motion-input version. This stance allows Chaos to move around freely, but he is unable to block while the gun is out. Using the motion input results in a close-range attack first. 12f wait time before the first shot can be fired. The reticle appears in a random location near the opponent before slowly tracking. The non-motion version of the input can be performed at any time during other moves except Throw, Roll (214K), Focus (214P), and Reload (22P)

a236sh.name: At The Ready (Fire)
a236sh.footer: Data in [ ] represents fully locked-on version. As long as Chaos has Ammo and Focus available, he can shoot at almost any time. Cannot fire during Focus, Reload, and most of Roll. Can be used while crouching by using 1H or 3H. 26f of  hit-stun. 24f of block-stun.

a2h.name: At The Ready (Cancel)
a2h.footer: You must use 2H, as inputting 1H or 3H will cause Chaos to fire.

a214s.name: Steady Aim
a214s.footer: Counter-hit state while in stance. Starts draining Concentration from frame 1. Reticle first appears on frame 18. Fire can be used starting on frame 19. Cancelable into Overdrives and Specials for the exception of At the Ready starting on frame 20. Blocking fully locked-on shots from this stance results in a Guard Crush.

a214sh.name: Steady Aim (Fire)
a214sh.footer: Data in [ ] represents fully locked-on version. 24f of block-stun when unfocused. 42f of Guard Crush block-stun when focused.

a214s214s.name: Steady Aim (Cancel)
a214s214s.footer: Now faster than reloading, but at the cost of not reloading.

a22p.name: Reload
a22p.footer: Reloads all spent bullets and can be freely canceled at any time after 23f. Each of the 6 bullets is reloaded on frames 21, 30, 39, 48, 57, and 66 respectively.

a214p.name: Focus
a214p.footer: Increases Concentration recovery rate and recovers a portion on use.

a214k.name: Roll
a214k.footer: Invul: Upper Body 4~15. Can pass through opponents on frames 1~18. Can Fire (At the Ready) towards the end of the animaiton.

a236k.name: Scapegoat
a236k.footer: Costs 15% of current health. Clone appears on frame 10, and lasts for 180 frames. Airborne frames 10~30. Counterhit recovery. At 1HP, the clone lasts 45 frames, and has a considerably shorter collision box.

a236p.name: Curse
a236p.footer: 5-second duration. Improves Reticle tracking. Airborne frames 7~19. Effect ends if Chaos takes damage.

a632146s.name: Deus Ex Machina
a632146s.footer: NOT a reversal. Requires Tension and Concentration to use. Fully reloads ammo. Chaos will exit the animation in his At the Ready stance.

a214214p.name: Super Focus
a214214p.footer: Refills Concentration and increases the recovery rate. Fast recovery means normals like 6K and 2D can be plus on block.

a5h.name: 5H
a5h.footer: Very disjointed hitbox. Wall-bounces on air-hit near corner.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a2h.name: 2H
a2h.footer: Hits low! Slight low profile frames 10~22.

ajd.name: j.D
ajd.footer: Halts Baiken's air-momentum, pushing her backwards. Wall-bounces near corner.

a6k.name: 6K
a6k.footer: 2-frame gap when canceled into from P or K normals. Lower hurtbox recedes slightly during startup.

a6h.name: 6H
a6h.footer: 4-frame gap when canceled into from c.S. Moderately disjointed hitbox.

a236k.name: Tatami Gaeshi
a236k.footer: Strike-type hitbox. On frames 15~30, Tatami can nullify any number of projectile hits, except versus Overdrives. Launches upwards on hit.

aj236k.name: Air Tatami Gaeshi
aj236k.footer: Behaves like a projectile and is active until it hits the ground.

a41236s.name: S Kabari
a41236s.footer: Tethers to the opponent on both hit and block. Tether effects grows stronger with distance.

a41236h.name: H Kabari
a41236h.footer: Pulls the opponent towards Baiken on both hit and block. Press or hold H to perform a followup slash.

a41236hh.name: H Kabari Follow-Up
a41236hh.footer: Data in [ ] refers to charged version. This followup can be used even on whiff. Can pass through opponents but does not hit crossup. Attack can be delayed by holding [H], which also extends the range. If blocked, Baiken is put into a Guard Crush state.

aj236s.name: Youzansen
aj236s.footer: Data in [ ] refers to earliest possible air input. Hits crossup. Doing so results in a soft KD. Incredibly fast overhead when using the instant-air input (9236S). TK Input can be done with 2369S as well, but this can result in a super-jump, which affects the data. Causes a slight float state on hit, so it has 'cancelable hitstun'. Your opponent can block but can't reversal out. More advantage when connecting on the way down from a jump.

a236p.name: Hiiragi
a236p.footer: Data in [ ] refers to a successful counter from far range. Being a counter, this move cannot be safe-jumped. Cannot parry projectiles, throws, or separate entities. Counter-hit recovery.

a236236s.name: Tsurane Sanzu-watashi
a236236s.footer: Invul: 1~8 Full. 7-frame gap between the 2nd and 3rd hit on block.

a214214p.name: Kenjyu
a214214p.footer: Firework explodes on contact with opponent/wall or at max distance, which is after 28 active frames.

aj214214p.name: Air Kenjyu
aj214214p.footer: When performed from the air, the projectile is shot at a downwards angle. Firework explodes on contact with opponent/wall or at max distance, which is after 28 active frames.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

ajd.name: j.D
ajd.footer: Halts air momentum and pushes backwards.

a236s.name: S Grave Reaper
a236s.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged. Only the first hit knocks down. Can be held to change projectile behaviour. Places Succubus. Only the first hit procs the Stain explosion.

a236h.name: H Grave Reaper
a236h.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged. Only the first hit knocks down. Can be held to change projectile behaviour. Places Succubus. Only the first hit procs the Stain explosion.

aj236s.name: Air S Grave Reaper
aj236s.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged. Only the first hit knocks down. Can be held to change projectile behaviour. Places Succubus. Only the first hit procs the Stain explosion.

aj236h.name: Air H Grave Reaper
aj236h.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged. Only the first hit knocks down. Can be held to change projectile behaviour. Places Succubus. Only the first hit procs the Stain explosion.

a214p.name: Unholy Diver
a214p.footer: Applies Stain State, but will not proc the explosion. Will fly to a placed Succubus. Can be forced to fly in a horizontal line by holding the button down.

a214k.name: Possession
a214k.footer: Counter-hit Recovery. Will teleport to a placed Succubus. Can be feinted by holding [K].

a236236p.name: Nostrovia
a236236p.footer: Applies Stain State. Considerable advantage on block.

a5d.name: 5D
a5d.footer: Data in [ ] represents values when fully charged.

a6h.name: 6H
a6h.footer: Airborne during duration. Wall-bounces near corner.

afss.name: f.SS
afss.footer: Can be used after f.S or 2S.

a236s.name: Forward S Stop and Dash
a236s.footer: 3f Recovery at max range. Travels horizontally. Cannot be used again while Yo-Yo is on-screen. Goes away when Bridget is hit.

a236h.name: Forward H Stop and Dash
a236h.footer: 3f Recovery at max range. Travels diagonally. Cannot be used again while Yo-Yo is on-screen. Goes away when Bridget is hit.

a214s.name: Backward S Stop and Dash
a214s.footer: Data in [ ] represents values of the Yo-Yo attack. Travels horizontally. Cannot be used again while Yo-Yo is on-screen. Goes away when Bridget is hit.

a214h.name: BackWard H Stop and Dash
a214h.footer: Data in [ ] represents values of the Yo-Yo attack. Travels diagonally. Cannot be used again while Yo-Yo is on-screen. Goes away when Bridget is hit.

a214k.name: Rolling Movement
a214k.footer: Can only be performed while a Yo-Yo is on-screen. Bridget will always travel towards the Yo-Yo. After initial startup, Bridget may cancel this move into any normal, special, or air-action. Attack can be delayed by holding down the [K] button.

aj63214p.name: Air Rock the Baby
aj63214p.footer: Move can be delayed by holding the [P] button, making air-to-ground grabs possible when Bridget lands. Otherwise, this move can only grab airborne opponents.

a632146s.name: Loop the Loop
a632146s.footer: Data in [ ] represents values for Roger, the bear.

a632146h.name: Return of the Killing Machine
a632146h.footer: Some proration applies on final hit.

ak632146h.name: Air Return of the Killing Machine
